ce:section.ce:para:
To explore the effects of ultrasonic cavitation on the pore structure of activated carbons, we prepared three samples (H-AC-180, H-AC-360, and H-AC-540) using the horn-based cavitation reactor. The N2 adsorption/desorption isotherms of H-AC-180 and H-AC-360 (Fig. 9
                           ) belonged to the combination of type Ib and type IVa, which indicated the presence of micropores and mesopores, whereas the isotherms of H-AC-540 were classified as type Ib, which proved the sample to be microporous. The pore parameters derived from the isotherms were presented in Table 1
                           . Two interesting results were observed.
